The paper deals with the problem of testing closeness between two distributions with unequal sized samples, which is a problem in statistics and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves analyzing the sample complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the problem of estimating the mixing time of a Markov chain, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
